# Controller Patterns and Conventions

## Controller Base Classes

### Authenticated Controllers

**ALL API controllers** (except AuthController) MUST extend `JwtAuthController`:

```php
<?php

namespace App\Http\Controllers;

use App\Models\Company;
use Illuminate\Http\JsonResponse;
use Illuminate\Http\Request;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Validator;

class CompanyController extends JwtAuthController
{
    private Company $model;

    public function __construct() {
        parent::__construct();
        $this->model = new Company();
    }

    // Controller methods...
}
```

### Available Properties

When extending `JwtAuthController`, you automatically have:
- `$this->user` - The authenticated user (from JWT token)
- `$this->error($message, $code)` - Helper for error responses

## Standard CRUD Controller Pattern

### Index (List) Method

```php
public function index(): JsonResponse
{
    $companyId = $this->user->company_id;
    
    // Role-based filtering (role_id 1 and 2 are admins)
    if (!$companyId || ($this->user->role_id == 1) || ($this->user->role_id == 2)) {
        $companies = $this->model::all();
    } else {
        $companies = [Company::find($companyId)];
    }
    
    return response()->json($companies);
}
```

### Store (Create) Method

```php
public function store(Request $request): JsonResponse
{
    $item = $request->all();
    
    // Validation
    $validator = Validator::make($item, [
        'code' => 'required',
        'registered_name' => 'required'
    ]);

    if ($validator->fails()) {
        return response()->json($validator->errors(), 422);
    }
    
    // Set defaults for optional fields
    if (!isset($item['tel'])) {
        $item['tel'] = '';
    }
    // ... more defaults
    
    // Create
    $company = $this->model->create($item);
    return response()->json($company);
}
```

### Show (Get Single) Method

```php
public function show($id): JsonResponse
{
    $company = $this->model->find($id);
    
    if (!$company) {
        return response()->json([
            'message' => 'Invalid company ID.',
        ], 404);
    }
    
    // Load relationships
    $sites = Site::where('company_id', $company->id)->get();
    $company->site = $sites;
    
    return response()->json($company);
}
```

### Update Method

```php
public function update(Request $request, $id): JsonResponse
{
    $item = $request->all();
    
    // Validation
    $validator = Validator::make($item, [
        'code' => 'required',
        'registered_name' => 'required'
    ]);

    if ($validator->fails()) {
        return response()->json($validator->errors(), 422);
    }
    
    $company = $this->model->find($id);
    if (!$company) {
        return response()->json(['status' => false, 'message' => 'Company ID not found'], 404);
    }
    
    // Set defaults
    $item['tel'] = $item['tel'] ?: '';
    // ... more defaults
    
    $company->update($item);
    return response()->json($company);
}
```

### Destroy (Delete) Method

```php
public function destroy($id): JsonResponse
{
    $item = $this->model->find($id);

    if (!$item) {
        return response()->json(['status' => false, 'message' => 'Company ID not found'], 404);
    }

    $item->delete();  // Soft delete if model uses SoftDeletes
    return response()->json(['status' => true]);
}
```

## Controller with Services

For complex operations, use Services:

```php
class WeighingHeadersController extends JwtAuthController
{
    private weighingHeaders $model;
    private WeighingHeaderService $headerService;

    public function __construct(
        WeighingHeaderService $headerService
    ) {
        parent::__construct();
        $this->model = new weighingHeaders();
        $this->headerService = $headerService;
    }

    public function index(): JsonResponse
    {
        // Delegate to service
        $weighingHeaders = $this->headerService->getWeighingHeaders(
            $companyId, $siteId, $workstationId, $status, 
            $pageStart, $pageSize, $orderByCol, $orderByDir, $searchTerm
        );
        
        return response()->json($weighingHeaders[0]);
    }
}
```

## Response Patterns

### Success Responses

```php
// Simple data
return response()->json($data);

// With status
return response()->json($data, 200);

// Status object
return response()->json(['status' => true, 'data' => $data]);
```

### Error Responses

```php
// Validation errors
return response()->json($validator->errors(), 422);

// Not found
return response()->json(['message' => 'Resource not found'], 404);

// Custom error
return response()->json(['status' => false, 'message' => 'Error message'], 400);

// Using helper method
return $this->error('Error message', 400);
```

## Request Data Handling

### Getting Request Data

```php
// All data
$data = $request->all();

// Specific field
$id = $request->input('id');

// With default
$pageSize = $request->input('pageSize', 500);

// From GET parameters
$companyId = $_GET['company_id'] ?? null;
```

### Setting Defaults

```php
// Check and set defaults
if (!isset($item['field'])) {
    $item['field'] = '';
}

// Or use null coalescing
$item['field'] = $item['field'] ?? '';
$item['field'] = $item['field'] ?: '';  // Empty string becomes ''
```

## Database Transactions

Use transactions for multi-step operations:

```php
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\DB;

$result = DB::transaction(function () use ($data) {
    // Multiple database operations
    $header = $this->headerService->insertWeighingHeader($data);
    $transaction = $this->transactionService->createWeighingTransaction($data);
    
    return $header;
}, 4);  // Retry 4 times on deadlock

return response()->json($result);
```

## Logging

Use Laravel's Log facade:

```php
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Log;

// Info logging
Log::info('Message', ['data' => $data]);
Log::info(print_r($data, true));

// Error logging
Log::error($e->getMessage());
Log::error("{$e->getMessage()}\n{$e->getTraceAsString()}");
```

## Critical Rules

1. **ALWAYS** extend `JwtAuthController` for authenticated endpoints
2. **ALWAYS** call `parent::__construct()` in constructor
3. **ALWAYS** validate request data before processing
4. **ALWAYS** return proper HTTP status codes
5. **ALWAYS** handle not found cases (404)
6. **ALWAYS** use Services for complex business logic
7. **ALWAYS** use database transactions for multi-step operations
8. **DO** use `response()->json()` for JSON responses
9. **DO** set defaults for optional fields
10. **DO** use try-catch for error handling when appropriate
